  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0ddc\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0ddc\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dc4\u0dbb\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0dba \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dd0\u0dba\u0dd2 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9c\u0db8 \u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dba\u0ddd \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0ddd\u0db0\u0dba\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Close employees are protesting that those who attacked the conductor should be arrested",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Nikaveratiya Sri Langama bus workers staged a protest today (04th) at the bus stop, demanding the immediate arrest of the suspects involved in the mob attack on the bus conductor who was trying to save a girl who had been abused in a Langama bus.",
        "A large number of bus workers started a continuous strike by stopping the schedules of about 40 buses belonging to the Nikaveratiya Sri Langama depot and parking all the buses at the Nikaveratiya bus stand.",
        "A girl who was traveling in the bus from Nikaveratiya to Rasnayakapura at around 7.00 p.m. said that she was being bothered by a person. After she moved to another seat, the conductor was attacked by that person and his relative in the bus. The conductor was hospitalized for four days. The bus workers said that they started this continuous strike because the suspects were not arrested.",
        "The bus workers said that the two suspects who attacked the bus conductor Janaka Bandara (38), a father of one, who is a resident of Kadigawa area and is in a serious condition at Nikaveratiya Hospital, in Udahenegama area, are arrested immediately and will not give up their fight until the law is enforced. mentioned",
        "In a social environment in which not only a young woman but also a little girl and even a mother cannot travel freely in buses, a bus worker should be appreciated for working to prevent such situations. The bus workers also emphasized to the authorities here.",
        "The Nikaveratiya Headquarters Police stated that these two suspects who are said to be involved in the incident have fled the area by now, several special police teams have been deployed to arrest them immediately, and the law has been strictly enforced against the relevant suspects.",
        "Due to the workers' strike, bus services were disrupted on all the routes starting from Nikaveratiya city and a large number of bus passengers were in great difficulty since the morning of 04 due to the bus strike and due to the fuel crisis there was heavy passenger traffic in the limited number of private buses."
      ],
